# About Section
about_title: WhoAmI
about_profile_image: images/portrait.jpg
about_content: | # this will include new lines to allow paragraphs
  Welcome! My name is Logan and this is my website where I post my most relevant work experience and display my technical knowledge. 
  Here you can find my [Resume](/assets/Logan Mancuso - ML Engineer.docx). My GitHub and GitLab are linked above with all of my contact information.
## Projects
content:
  - title: Projects # Title for the section
    layout: list # Type of content section (list/text)
    content:
      - layout: left
        border: weak  # Value of `weak` will display a weak border below this item. # Any 
                      # other value (or no value) means no border will be displayed
        title: MIRC Facial Recognition
        # link: https://github.com/loganmancuso/MIRC_Facial
        # link_text: Link Text
        additional_links:
          - title:  Github
            icon: fab fa-github
            url: https://gitlab.com/loganmancuso_USCRCi
        quote: >
          World War II Facial Recognition Program
        description: | # this will include new lines to allow paragraphs
          This program will utilize OpenCV and Caffe to parse video files into still images.  It will then take the still images and search for faces and crop the images to a ROI (region of interest) for the model to match.  The model will take the know faces and names and attempt to match the still images to the names, creating a database of names and time stamps. This will allow the user to know where in each video each person appears
## Experience
  - title: Experience
    layout: list
    content:
      - layout: left
        title: Panera - Capgemini
        sub_title: Lead API Developer
        caption: 2019
        # link: Link to company (optional)
        quote: >
          Panera Bread Co. partnered with Capgemini to develop a resful API for their fleet of service vehicles and external meal delivery systems
        description: | # this will include new lines to allow paragraphs
          Lead Developer over 4 team members; quality checked their work to build 250 endpoints. Was responsible for 150 on my own and successfully delivered the API's on time to the client.  
          Key Tools - Apigee (Google Cloud Platform), Swagger.
      - layout: left
        title: HCSC - Capgemini
        sub_title: API Developer
        caption: 2020
        # link: Link to company (optional)
        quote: >
          This insurance company partnered with Capgemini to translate legacy mainframe IBM message queing to a modern REST based API
        description: | # this will include new lines to allow paragraphs
          Lead developer for a team, and was responsible to helping architect the platform, which encryption schemas to use and how the message queing would work in the system post cutover. 
          Key Tools - Mulesoft, Swagger, IBMMQ
      - layout: left
        title: Idemia (Civil ID & MBIS) - Capgemini
        sub_title: Lead DevOps Engineer, Lead Application Engrineer, and Lead Tier 3 Support
        caption: 2020 - Present
        # link: Link to company (optional)
        quote: >
          Idemia partnered with Capgemini to accomplish a few goals: To achive full Real-ID compliance by 2020, and to have full server based system and upgrade from their mainframe. 
        description: | # this will include new lines to allow paragraphs
          Our Client was the Oklahoma Department of Public Safety. They had tasked Idemia and Capgemini with a massive undertaking. A team of around 15-20 Developers and Managers and Myself as the Devlead took this task on and accomplished that goal on Feburary 28th 2022. This project has been such a massive part of my life and has taught me more about computing than any project to-date. 
          Key Tools - Octopus, Jenkins, JFrog, Microsoft CRM Dynamics 365, MoveIT, Pentaho, SQL, Informatica, Microsoft PowerBI 
      - layout: left
        title: University of SC Research Computing
        sub_title: HPC & Nerual Network Developer
        caption: 2015 - 2019
        link: https://usc-rc.github.io/
        quote: >
          A research division with the goal of helping researchers accomplish their goals using high performance computing
        description: | # this will include new lines to allow paragraphs
          High Performance Computing, helping research students adapt software to utilize OpenMPi for scaling projects across multiple nodes. Utilizing Anaconda environments and Modules to create flexible local development. SLURM scheduling to optimize program submission and resource allocation for thousands of processes. Python development for machine learning using OpenCV3 for facial recognition and TensorFlow to train AI models. 
          Key Tools - SLURM, OpenMpi, TensorFlow, Anaconda, Python, OpenCV
